Employee Acknowledgement Comments: In reviewing my Employee Performance Review, it is my belief that there a few inaccurate details indicated.Competency 2 of 8As it relates to the demonstration of my reliability, loyalty and professionalism, I have shown a significant amount of compliance in this area.  There has not been one time where I was expected to complete a task or demonstrate my loyalty and professionalism and did not do so proficiently. With this being said I believe my review should have at least been a 4.Competency 3 of 8Ra'Jah's comment stated that I should "work more on accuracy in work submitted". However, I cannot recall a time where I submitted anything, and it was inaccurate. The only situation I can think of that may relate to this topic is when I sent an email and forgot to add the attachment, in which I sent immediately upon recognition. Competency 4 of 8"Employee demonstrates job relevant knowledge and essential skills, such as work practices, company policies, resources, procedures, and technical information, as well as the relationship of work to the organization’s mission as related to the job description. Also measured are employee’s self-improvement efforts to enhance skills and knowledge base to remain current on changes that impact the job per AGB policy and procedures/directive."I scored a "2 needs Improvement To Meet Performance Standards" This left me befuddled because not only am I familiar with the components mentioned  regarding my position, I mastered it! I went beyond my job description to even draw diagrams on correct policies and procedures as it relates to my job description that was verbally communicated to me, because I never received a physical copy of what this position requires as previously requested. The second part of this statement says " Also measured are employee’s self-improvement efforts to enhance skills and knowledge base" I always go beyond to learn more about any position I am placed in along with identifying ways to make it better. If there is anything I am not knowledgeable about in this position, it is because I was not accurately informed and guided through the process. However, I am ALWAYS yearning to learn more because Knowledge is Power.Competency 7 of 8Her comment stated she would love to see more "business casual" from me. I have always dressed within company policy, but when I started with Procurement, she spoke with me and said how I should dress business professional more within this position, which is what I did. But, at the end of her statement she said "Professionalism is key esp when attending meetings." Even though this was just a statement, it is an indication that I do not dress professional when attending meetings and I definitely do. Always! So, this comment left me with some slight confusion. Competency 8 of 8I was graded at a 3 for Meeting the Performance Standard, the first part of her comment backed that up stating "Erin has done at great job at finding up to 10-20 opportunities a month. She is actively pursuing work on local, state and federal level. She is gainfully employed in regards to ensuring the Procurement goals are met." However, the truth is I have exceeded this goal. I was pushing out beyond the number of opportunities I was supposed to find, and she ask me to "slow down, because she couldn't keep up". This is understandable because a personalized proposal must be sent out for each opportunity. However, I should be graded on the reality of the work that I was putting out, not just the amount of work that she requested for me to complete. She also stated she "would love for me to take a writing class" but to my knowledge nothing is wrong with my writing skills, nor has she ever pulled me to the side to address any errors. One can always learn more, but I have great writing skills to my knowledge.Overall, Ra'Jah is a great manager, but her review does not reflect our work relationship nor my work effort.
